re going.  Please by all means feel free to correct me, as I am probably wrong in my assumptions, but its still worth figuring out.<br>
<br>
Okay, was just noticing that a lot of the time when im raiding or grouping if I have been sitting down afk, or attacking another mob etc, then move to a mob that has say 1/2 its health left, and then try to taunt it...it almost always takes up to 3 or 4 taunts to get that mob to turn on me, whereas if it is a newly pulled mob, the first taunt usually does it.<br>
<br>
I can't figure if this means that it is just harder to taunt of a mob that has been dmg a lot by others becuase they built up so much hate while fighting, or that im just really frikin unlucky when it comes to my tuant skill working.<br>
<br>
Anyways, please let me know what u think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fvighlander>Fvighlander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/03 5:45:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3050.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Another new slant on taunt...mebbe</span><hr size=1> I'd say that normal taunt (not AE taunt) has some maximum amount of aggro that it can add in a single use.... meaning if you're more than XXX number of points down the hate list, taunt just plain isn't going to work, period. I've seen the same sort of behavior you did vanax, and some other situations that are similar as well.... examples<br>
<br>
Exp grouping anywhere in PoP. If I've melee'ed for about 6-7 seconds before the slow lands (or if the slow is quicker but I land a lucky taunting blow proc first), the slower will get aggro, but one taunt gets the mob back on me, damn near every time. If a mob gets slowed in less than 4-5 seconds and I haven't proc'ed yet, takes 2 taunts, every time.<br>
<br>
I've never been able to get aggro on a mob that I haven't been fighting from the start without either some lucky chain procs to play catch-up, or using AE taunt (which obviously has no upper limit whatsoever... you hit the button, mob is pissed)<br>
<br>
Alternatively, it could be simply that your chance of a successful taunt gets lower and lower based on how far up the hate list you need to move. That could generate some of the same situations and success rates over time that we've mentioned, but I would think that sooner or later, you'd have to see that lucky taunt that gets aggro first shot on a mob that you haven't touched yet. I've never seen that happen...<br>
<br>
I talk this over with warrior friends sometimes when I'm bored. Some agree, some repeat the description of taunt that we've all known for years, doesn't matter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I know that I can intuitively know right about when a taunt 'should' work 90 percent of the time, and when it's gonna take me multiple taunts (or an AE) to get aggro, after grinding out exp and raiding for so long as a tank. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=573077" target="_blank">Fvighlander</a><br>
Overlord of <a href="http://www.final-destiny.org" target="_blank">Final Destiny</a><br>
