As an example, if you are trying to take aggro from someone who has been tanking a mob already for a minute or two, if you just walk up and Taunt, the chance of success is very small (perhaps 1% or less). But as you start meleeing the mob, by the time Taunt refreshes perhaps you then have a 10% chance of success, and by the next refresh, perhaps a 25% chance.<br>
I don't think Taunt in-and-of-itself generates a set amount of hate; I think it either succeeds (puts you on top of hatelist by a small margin) or does nothing. It is perhaps possible that even an unsuccessful taunt adds a % chance to the next Taunt.<br>
